Assent Compliance is the global leader in supply chain data management. We combine leading-edge technology with supply chain expertise to help companies collect and manage the data they need to comply with global requirements and make ethical business decisions. As the leader in a new industry, we’re growing fast, and we’re looking for customer focused, solutions-first people to join our team!

Based in Columbus, Ohio, the Data Consulting Specialist will have a wide range of duties; all of which are in the spirit of ensuring customer success through the successful support of client data. As part of Assent’s Data Consulting team, the Data Consulting Specialist will play an integral role in managing client data and implementations in the Assent Platform.

You'll be working on:
Providing in-depth support for data related questions or concerns to internal and external stakeholders;
Analyzing data sets to proactively identify potential concerns or delays;
Creating and leading data implementation strategies to ensure effective implementation of new client data;
Investigating client concerns regarding data structure or appearance in the Assent Platform;
Supporting the Customer Experience team in interactions with clients to provide updates, communicate concerns, or clarify discrepancies in regards to client data;
Join us if you are:
Experienced with a Bachelor's Degree in Management Information Systems, Computer Science, Statistics, Mathematics, Engineering, Business, or other relevant areas;
Knowledgeable from advanced to expert on data manipulation tools, such as Microsoft Excel, SQL, or Python;
Committed to providing excellent customer support over the phone and email, representing Assent in the most positive, professional, and effective way;
Excellent with oral and written communication skills in English - you communicate clearly, concisely, and with tact;
Superior with your interpersonal skills - you are able to establish effective cross-functional relationships in a collaborative environment with a diverse group of internal and external stakeholders.
What’s in it for you?

At Assent, we are an ambitious, fast-paced business which means there is never a dull moment. We strive to give back to our employees as much as they give to us.

In addition to a competitive salary, a benefits plan that starts the same day you do, and a fantastic office in a central location, you can expect to:
Work for one of the fastest-growing technology companies in North America!
Love what you do as part of a supportive and collaborative team with a fantastic culture
Do purposeful, meaningful work towards better ethical and environmental conditions around the world
Help create positive change by being part of a sustainable work environment with lots of opportunity to help the local community through our charitable work.
At Assent, your contribution has purpose. Our team challenges each other to be better every day; we dig deep to build a culture of innovation and high performance for our people and our clients.

All applicants will need to fulfill the requirements necessary to obtain a background check.

